{#- Plan generation prompt for structured test-suite guidance. -#}
{% from "_macros.jinja2" import constraints_dump %}
You are a test-generation architect. Write a detailed generation plan that a coding agent will follow to produce pytest test suites.

The plan must be a Markdown document with one section per task. For each task, specify:
1. **File structure** — module docstring, imports, named constants
2. **Test function template** — exact docstring format, decorator patterns, return annotations
3. **Required test categories** — numbered list of behavior groups to cover (spec examples, edge cases, error cases, round-trip properties)
4. **Constraint compliance** — specific instructions for satisfying each constraint (how to write docstrings, how to avoid magic numbers, etc.)

## Objective: {{ objective.name }}

Description: {{ objective.description }}

{% if objective.target_files %}
Target files: {{ objective.target_files | map("tojson") | join(", ") }}

{% endif %}
{% for task in effective_tasks %}
### Task: {{ task.name }}
{% if task.description %}
Description: {{ task.description }}
{% endif %}
{% if task.signature %}
Signature: `{{ task.signature }}`
{% endif %}
{% if task.train_evals %}
Train evals:
{% for ev in task.train_evals %}
  - {{ task.name }}({{ ev.input }}) -> {{ ev.output }}
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
{% if constraints_data.get(task.name) %}
{% set cd = constraints_data[task.name] %}
Constraints:
{{ constraints_dump(cd.primary_dump, cd.secondary_dump, cd.guidance) }}
{% endif %}

{% endfor %}
IMPORTANT: The plan must be detailed enough that a coding agent can produce a constraint-compliant test file on the FIRST attempt. Be explicit about docstring format (Google-style with Args section), magic number avoidance (named constants), and function length limits.

Output ONLY the Markdown plan. No code blocks, no preamble.